==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Latin]] ''sinister'' "left hand".

===Adjective===
'''sinister''' 

# evil, seeming to be evil
# In [[heraldry]], the left side of a shield from the wearer's standpoint, and the right side to the viewer.

====Antonym====
*[[dexter]]

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[pahaenteinen]] (1), [[uhkaava]] (1)

